  "title": "Site Engineer x 5 (Entry Level)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Assist in daily site operations, ensuring construction works are executed according to plans and schedules.</li><li>Coordinate with Professional Engineers, consultants (QPS), and subcontractors to address technical matters and support smooth site activities.</li><li>Resolve on-site engineering and technical issues promptly, while upholding required quality and safety standards.</li><li>Conduct site inspections, prepare reports, and develop method statements when required.</li><li>Monitor and guide site personnel to maintain orderly work areas and ensure progress aligns with project timelines.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering or a related discipline.</li><li><strong>Open to entry-level candidates</strong> with strong interest in site engineering and construction management.</li><li>Good understanding of construction methodologies, drawings, and basic engineering principles.</li><li>Strong communication and coordination skills when dealing with consultants, subcontractors, and site teams.</li><li>Proactive, willing to learn, and able to work in a fast-paced site environment.</li></ul><p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p><p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p><p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p><p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
